<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Amiga Screw Reference — A500 · A600 · A1200</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #f4f1eb;
    --bg-card: #ffffff;
    --bg-nav: #2c2a26;
    --bg-nav-hover: #3d3a34;
    --bg-nav-active: #4a4640;
    --text: #2c2a26;
    --text-muted: #7a756c;
    --text-nav: #c8c3b8;
    --text-nav-active: #f4f1eb;
    --accent: #c45a2d;
    --accent-light: #faeee8;
    --border: #ddd8ce;
    --teal: #1d9e75;
    --teal-bg: #e1f5ee;
    --blue: #2d6ab5;
    --blue-bg: #e6f1fb;
    --amber: #ba7517;
    --amber-bg: #faeeda;
    --red-bg: #fcebeb;
    --red: #a32d2d;
    --font-body: 'DM Sans', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    --radius: 10px;
    --radius-sm: 6px;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; scroll-padding-top: 2rem; }

  body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    display: flex;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* ─── Left navigation ─── */
  nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 260px;
    height: 100vh;
    background: var(--bg-nav);
    padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    z-index: 10;
    overflow-y: auto;
  }

  nav .logo {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  nav .subtitle {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  nav .nav-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  nav a {
    display: block;
    color: var(--text-nav);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }

  nav a:hover { background: var(--bg-nav-hover); color: var(--text-nav-active); }
  nav a.active { background: var(--bg-nav-active); color: var(--text-nav-active); }

  nav a .model-chip {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    background: rgba(196,90,45,0.2);
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-right: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  nav .spacer { flex: 1; }

  nav .nav-footer {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }

  /* ─── Main content ─── */
  main {
    margin-left: 260px;
    flex: 1;
    padding: 3rem 3.5rem 4rem;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  /* Stats bar */
  .stats-bar {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .stat-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 16px 20px;
  }

  .stat-card .stat-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .stat-card .stat-value {
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
  }

  .stat-card .stat-detail {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  /* Model sections */
  .model-section {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .model-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--text);
  }

  .model-header h2 {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }

  .model-header .badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    background: var(--accent-light);
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  /* Tables */
  .screw-table-wrap {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  thead th {
    text-align: left;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.02);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  tbody td {
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }

  tbody tr:hover { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.015); }

  .placement-note {
    display: block;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  /* Pills */
  .pill {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .pill-6mm { background: var(--teal-bg); color: var(--teal); }
  .pill-8mm { background: var(--blue-bg); color: var(--blue); }
  .pill-special { background: var(--amber-bg); color: var(--amber); }

  /* Notes & warnings */
  .info-box {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .info-box.note {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .info-box.warning {
    background: var(--amber-bg);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
    color: #5a3e0a;
  }

  .info-box strong { font-weight: 600; }

  /* Common specs footer */
  .common-section {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .common-section h3 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .common-section p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .common-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .common-section li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 6px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .common-section li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .common-section li .li-label {
    font-weight: 600;
    min-width: 100px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    nav { display: none; }
    main { margin-left: 0; padding: 2rem 1.25rem; }
    .stats-bar { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <div class="logo">Amiga Screws</div>
  <div class="subtitle">Hardware reference for the classic Commodore Amiga desktop models</div>

  <div class="nav-label">Models</div>
  <a href="#a500"><span class="model-chip">A500</span> Amiga 500</a>
  <a href="#a600"><span class="model-chip">A600</span> Amiga 600</a>
  <a href="#a1200"><span class="model-chip">A1200</span> Amiga 1200</a>

  <div class="nav-label" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Reference</div>
  <a href="#common">Common specifications</a>

  <div class="spacer"></div>
  <div class="nav-footer">
    All screw specifications based on original Commodore factory hardware. Variations may exist across production runs and revisions.
  </div>
</nav>

<main>
  <h1>Amiga screw reference</h1>
  <p class="page-subtitle">Case, motherboard and floppy drive screw types, sizes and placement for the A500, A600 and A1200.</p>

  <div class="stats-bar">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-label">A500 / 500+</div>
      <div class="stat-value">10</div>
      <div class="stat-detail">6 case + 4 motherboard</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-label">A600</div>
      <div class="stat-value">6</div>
      <div class="stat-detail">6 case (no separate MB screws)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-label">A1200</div>
      <div class="stat-value">10</div>
      <div class="stat-detail">7 case + 3 motherboard</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ════════ A500 ════════ -->
  <section class="model-section" id="a500">
    <div class="model-header">
      <h2>Amiga 500 / 500+</h2>
      <span class="badge">10 screws</span>
    </div>

    <div class="screw-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Qty</th><th>Size</th><th>Type</th><th>Placement</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>3</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-6mm">M3 × 6 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips, convex head</td>
            <td>Case bottom — front edge
              <span class="placement-note">Underside, along the front lip of the case</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>3</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-8mm">M3 × 8 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips, convex head</td>
            <td>Case bottom — rear edge
              <span class="placement-note">Underside, along the back of the case</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>4</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-6mm">M3 × 6 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips</td>
            <td>Motherboard mounting
              <span class="placement-note">2× at front, 2× at left side</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box note">
      The metal RF shielding is held by 4 Phillips screws plus bent metal clips. The floppy drive uses 4 separate screws (1 side + 3 from bottom) with a different thread — do not mix these with case screws. Some early A500 units used <strong>Torx T9</strong> or hex-socket (Allen) screws externally instead of Phillips.
    </div>
    <div class="info-box warning">
      <strong>Case bump warning:</strong> Using 8 mm screws in the front holes risks creating raised, discoloured marks on the top shell from over-tightening. Always use 6 mm screws for the front.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════ A600 ════════ -->
  <section class="model-section" id="a600">
    <div class="model-header">
      <h2>Amiga 600</h2>
      <span class="badge">6 screws</span>
    </div>

    <div class="screw-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Qty</th><th>Size</th><th>Type</th><th>Placement</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>6</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-6mm">M3 × 6 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips</td>
            <td>Case bottom — all six positions
              <span class="placement-note">All visible when flipped over; no screws behind the Commodore sticker</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box note">
      The A600 case also uses <strong>two side clips</strong> — one on the left near the floppy slot and one on the right near the PCMCIA port — that must be released with a flat screwdriver after removing the screws. The motherboard is not separately screwed down; it rests on standoffs held in place by the case halves. The floppy drive and hard disk caddy have their own separate mounting hardware.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════ A1200 ════════ -->
  <section class="model-section" id="a1200">
    <div class="model-header">
      <h2>Amiga 1200</h2>
      <span class="badge">10 screws</span>
    </div>

    <div class="screw-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Qty</th><th>Size</th><th>Type</th><th>Placement</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>3</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-6mm">M3 × 6 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips, convex head</td>
            <td>Case bottom — front edge
              <span class="placement-note">Underside, along front lip</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>2</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-8mm">M3 × 8 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips</td>
            <td>Case bottom — rear edge
              <span class="placement-note">Above the mouse and joystick ports</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>2</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-8mm">M3 × 8 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips</td>
            <td>Case sides
              <span class="placement-note">1× left side by floppy drive, 1× right side by PCMCIA slot</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>3</td>
            <td><span class="pill pill-6mm">M3 × 6 mm</span></td>
            <td>Phillips</td>
            <td>Motherboard mounting
              <span class="placement-note">1× front, 2× right side — varies by PCB revision</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box note">
      <strong>Rev 1D.4 motherboards</strong> lack the rightmost PCB section (mouse port area), so the floppy drive bracket and one motherboard screw position shift slightly left compared to earlier revisions. The bottom-left motherboard screw may use a metal flap or nut underneath. The internal floppy drive is secured by <strong>2 separate bolts</strong> (M3 × 8 mm) through the rear of the case above the joystick/mouse ports.
    </div>
    <div class="info-box warning">
      <strong>Case bump warning:</strong> As with the A500, never use 8 mm screws in the front case holes — 6 mm only to prevent damage to the top shell.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════ Common ════════ -->
  <section class="common-section" id="common">
    <h3>Common specifications across all models</h3>
    <p>All case and motherboard screws share the same M3 thread and Phillips head across the A500, A600 and A1200. Floppy drive mounting screws are separate hardware with different dimensions.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><span class="li-label">Thread</span> M3 (3 mm diameter, ~0.5 mm pitch)</li>
      <li><span class="li-label">Head type</span> Phillips (#2 driver) — convex / pan head</li>
      <li><span class="li-label">Short screw</span> 6 mm — front case holes and motherboard</li>
      <li><span class="li-label">Long screw</span> 8 mm (7.5–7.9 mm original) — rear and side case holes</li>
      <li><span class="li-label">Material</span> Steel (originals) or stainless steel (replacements)</li>
      <li><span class="li-label">Key rule</span> Always use 6 mm in front holes to avoid case bumps</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</main>

<script>
  // Highlight active nav link on scroll
  const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.model-section, .common-section');
  const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('nav a');

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        navLinks.forEach(link => link.classList.remove('active'));
        const active = document.querySelector(`nav a[href="#${entry.target.id}"]`);
        if (active) active.classList.add('active');
      }
    });
  }, { rootMargin: '-20% 0px -60% 0px' });

  sections.forEach(s => observer.observe(s));
</script>

</body>
</html>
